601	## 2. Anatomy
602	
603	```text
604	ScrollArea
605	├── Root           <div>   data-ars-state data-ars-overflow-x data-ars-overflow-y
606	│   ├── Viewport   <div>   role="region" tabindex="0" (native scroll)
607	│   │   └── Content <div>  (inner content wrapper)
608	│   ├── ScrollbarY <div>   role="none" (vertical track)
609	│   │   └── ThumbY <div>   role="none" (vertical thumb)
610	│   ├── ScrollbarX <div>   role="none" (horizontal track)
611	│   │   └── ThumbX <div>   role="none" (horizontal thumb)
612	│   └── CornerSquare <div> role="none" (gap filler when both axes)
613	```
614	
615	| Part         | Element | Key Attributes                                      |
616	| ------------ | ------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
617	| Root         | `<div>` | `data-ars-state`, `data-ars-overflow-x/y`           |
618	| Viewport     | `<div>` | `role="region"`, `tabindex="0"`, `aria-label`       |
619	| Content      | `<div>` | Inner content wrapper                               |
620	| ScrollbarY   | `<div>` | `role="none"`, `data-ars-visible`                   |
621	| ThumbY       | `<div>` | `role="none"`, sized/positioned by thumb metrics    |
622	| ScrollbarX   | `<div>` | `role="none"`, `data-ars-visible`                   |
623	| ThumbX       | `<div>` | `role="none"`, sized/positioned by thumb metrics    |
624	| CornerSquare | `<div>` | `role="none"`, visible when both scrollbars present |
625	
626	## 3. Accessibility
627	
628	### 3.1 ARIA Roles, States, and Properties
629	
630	| Element           | Attribute    | Value                                                   |
631	| ----------------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
632	| Viewport          | `role`       | `"region"`                                              |
633	| Viewport          | `aria-label` | Consumer-provided label                                 |
634	| Viewport          | `tabindex`   | `"0"` (focusable for keyboard scrolling)                |
635	| Scrollbars/Thumbs | `role`       | `"none"` (decorative; screen readers use native scroll) |
636	
637	- Custom scrollbar tracks and thumbs are decorative duplicates of the native scroll mechanism. They use `role="none"` (ARIA 1.2) to be excluded from the accessibility tree.
638	- Keyboard users scroll the viewport using standard browser key behaviours (arrow keys, Page Up/Down, Space).
639	- No `tabindex` is placed on scrollbar elements.
640	
641	## 4. Internationalization
642	
643	### 4.1 Messages
644	
645	```rust
646	#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
647	pub struct Messages {
648	    pub viewport_label: MessageFn<dyn Fn(&Locale) -> String + Send + Sync>,
649	}
650	
651	impl Default for Messages {
652	    fn default() -> Self {
653	        Self { viewport_label: MessageFn::static_str("Scrollable content") }
654	    }
655	}
656	
657	impl ComponentMessages for Messages {}
658	```
659	
660	### 4.2 RTL Support
661	
662	**Vertical scrollbar position:** In `dir="rtl"`, `data-ars-dir="rtl"` is set on Root. CSS targets this to move the vertical scrollbar to the left side:
663	
664	```css
665	[data-ars-dir="rtl"] [data-ars-part="scrollbar-y"] {
666	    right: auto;
667	    left: 0;
668	}
669	```
670	
671	**Horizontal scroll normalization:** RTL browsers use different `scrollLeft` conventions. The machine normalizes to a 0-to-positive range:
672	
673	```rust
674	/// Normalizes `scrollLeft` across browser RTL conventions.
675	/// - Standard (Chrome, Firefox >= 112): negative values, 0 at left edge
676	/// - Legacy Firefox (< 112): negative values, 0 at right edge
677	/// - Safari/WebKit: positive values, 0 at right edge
678	///
679	/// Returns normalized value in range [0, scrollWidth - clientWidth].
680	fn normalize_scroll_left(raw: f64, scroll_width: f64, client_width: f64, is_rtl: bool) -> f64 {
681	    if !is_rtl {
682	        return raw;
683	    }
684	    // Detect convention by checking sign of scrollLeft at initial position
685	    // Modern standard: raw <= 0, normalize to positive range
686	    if raw <= 0.0 {
687	        raw.abs()
688	    } else {
689	        // Safari positive convention: already positive
690	        scroll_width - client_width - raw
691	    }
692	}
693	```
694	
695	## 5. Library Parity
696	
697	> Compared against: Ark UI (`ScrollArea`), Radix UI (`ScrollArea`).
698	
699	### 5.1 Props
700	
701	| Feature                   | ars-ui                           | Ark UI                  | Radix UI                | Notes                                            |
702	| ------------------------- | -------------------------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
703	| Scrollbar visibility mode | `scrollbar_visibility` (4 modes) | --                      | `type` (4 modes)        | Same semantics, different naming                 |
704	| Hide delay                | `hide_delay_ms`                  | --                      | `scrollHideDelay`       | Same feature                                     |
705	| Direction (RTL)           | `dir`                            | --                      | `dir`                   | Same feature                                     |
706	| CSP nonce                 | --                               | --                      | `nonce`                 | Adapter-level concern in ars-ui; not a core prop |
707	| Orientation               | `orientation`                    | Scrollbar `orientation` | Scrollbar `orientation` | ars-ui sets at Root; refs set per-scrollbar      |
708	| Min thumb size            | `min_thumb_size`                 | --                      | --                      | ars-ui addition                                  |
709	| Accessible label          | `aria_label`                     | --                      | --                      | ars-ui addition                                  |
710	
711	**Gaps:** None. `nonce` is handled at the adapter layer.
712	
713	### 5.2 Anatomy
714	
715	| Part                   | ars-ui         | Ark UI      | Radix UI    | Notes                               |
716	| ---------------------- | -------------- | ----------- | ----------- | ----------------------------------- |
717	| Root                   | `Root`         | `Root`      | `Root`      | --                                  |
718	| Viewport               | `Viewport`     | `Viewport`  | `Viewport`  | --                                  |
719	| Content                | `Content`      | `Content`   | --          | Radix nests content inside Viewport |
720	| Scrollbar (vertical)   | `ScrollbarY`   | `Scrollbar` | `Scrollbar` | ars-ui splits per-axis              |
721	| Scrollbar (horizontal) | `ScrollbarX`   | `Scrollbar` | `Scrollbar` | ars-ui splits per-axis              |
722	| Thumb (vertical)       | `ThumbY`       | `Thumb`     | `Thumb`     | ars-ui splits per-axis              |
723	| Thumb (horizontal)     | `ThumbX`       | `Thumb`     | `Thumb`     | ars-ui splits per-axis              |
724	| Corner                 | `CornerSquare` | `Corner`    | `Corner`    | Same feature                        |
725	
726	**Gaps:** None.
727	
728	### 5.3 Events
729	
730	| Callback        | ars-ui                    | Ark UI | Radix UI | Notes                |
731	| --------------- | ------------------------- | ------ | -------- | -------------------- |
732	| Scroll position | `Event::Scroll`           | --     | --       | State machine event  |
733	| Resize          | `Event::Resize`           | --     | --       | State machine event  |
734	| Thumb drag      | `ThumbDragStart/Move/End` | --     | --       | State machine events |
735	| Track click     | `Event::TrackClick`       | --     | --       | State machine event  |
736	
737	**Gaps:** None. Ark UI and Radix UI handle these internally without exposing callbacks.
738	
739	### 5.4 Features
740	
741	| Feature                   | ars-ui                                           | Ark UI                                           | Radix UI |
742	| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------ | -------- |
743	| Custom scrollbar styling  | Yes                                              | Yes                                              | Yes      |
744	| Four visibility modes     | Yes                                              | --                                               | Yes      |
745	| Drag-to-scroll (thumb)    | Yes                                              | Yes                                              | Yes      |
746	| Track click (page scroll) | Yes                                              | Yes                                              | Yes      |
747	| RTL support               | Yes                                              | --                                               | Yes      |
748	| Scroll position queries   | `is_at_top/bottom/left/right`, `scroll_progress` | `isAtTop/Bottom/Left/Right`, `getScrollProgress` | --       |
749	| Scroll-to APIs            | --                                               | `scrollToEdge`, `scrollTo`                       | --       |
750	
751	**Gaps:** Ark UI exposes `scrollToEdge` and `scrollTo` imperative APIs. These are adapter-level operations (calling `element.scrollTo()`) rather than state machine concerns. Adapters can provide these as utility methods on the framework wrapper without core spec changes.
752	
753	### 5.5 Summary
754	
755	- **Overall:** Full parity.
756	- **Divergences:** ars-ui splits scrollbars into per-axis parts (`ScrollbarY`/`ScrollbarX`) instead of parameterized `Scrollbar(orientation)`. This is more explicit and avoids runtime orientation checks.
757	- **Recommended additions:** None.
